title: Thompson & Knight Welcomes New Associates
text:
Thompson & Knight LLP
DALLAS, Oct. 5, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ -- Thompson & Knight LLP welcomes 13 Associates. State Bar of Texas admission is anticipated fall 2015.
Austin Office
Nathan K. Palmer (Government and Regulatory, Trial) J.D. (2015) from Harvard Law School and M.S. (2009) and B.A., magna cum laude , (2007) from Brigham Young University
Dallas Office
John Atkins (Trial) J.D., magna cum laude , (2015) from SMU Dedman School of Law and B.A. (2006) from Willamette University
Matthew Cornelia (Intellectual Property) J.D. (2015) from The University of Texas School of Law and B.S. (2010) from The University of Texas at Arlington
Christopher O. Dachniwsky (Trial) J.D., James Kent Scholar, (2015) from Columbia Law School and B.A., magna cum laude , (2012) from Texas A&M University
Alexander T. Dimock (Trial) J.D., magna cum laude , (2014) from Duke University School of Law and B.S., summa cum laude , (2010) from University of North Carolina at Greensboro
Brooke Donnelly (Real Estate and Banking) J.D., with honors, and M.B.A. (2015) from University of Oklahoma College of Law & Price College of Business and B.A. (2005) from University of Oklahoma
Samuel E. Fubara (Oil and Gas) J.D. (2015) from Northwestern University School of Law and B.A. (2011) from Georgetown University
Kathleen V. Wade (Bankruptcy, Trial) J.D. and LL.M. (2015) from Duke University School of Law and B.A., magna cum laude , (2012) from Furman University
Houston Office
Cesar G. Leyva (Corporate and Securities) J.D. (2015) from The University of Texas School of Law and B.B.A. (2012) from The University of Texas at Austin
V. Parker Pritchett (Finance) J.D., summa cum laude , (2015) from Texas Tech University School of Law and B.A. (2012) from Washington and Lee University
Monica J. Raspino (Corporate and Securities) J.D., magna cum laude , (2015) from University of Houston Law Center and B.S., high honors, (2012) from The University of Texas at Austin
Ayomide O. Shittu (Bankruptcy and Restructuring) J.D. (2015) from The University of Texas School of Law and B.A., magna cum laude , (2011) from Sam Houston State University
New York Office
Mo Tavakoli (Real Estate and Banking) J.D., cum laude , (2015) from New York Law School and B.A. (2011) from Ryerson University
About Thompson & Knight
Established in 1887, Thompson & Knight is a full-service law firm with more than 300 attorneys who provide legal solutions to clients around the world. Visit www.tklaw.com for more.
